articles.author: Vivian Sequera, Mircely Guanipa
articles.description: Venezuelan opposition parties and their supporters were holding protests around the country on Thursday in an eleventh-hour effort to put pressure on President Nicolas Maduro, one day before he is due to be sworn in for his third six-year term.
articles.title: As Maduro inauguration looms, Venezuela opposition hold street protests

articles.author: Rollo Ross, Jackie Luna
articles.description: Wildfires raged deep into the storied heartland of the American film industry.
articles.title: Hollywood Hills burn as LA engulfed by 'the big one'

articles.author: Hyunjoo Jin, Hyonhee Shin
articles.description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol's security chief said on Friday the impeached leader, who faces arrest over a criminal probe into his Dec. 3 martial law bid, has been unfairly treated for a sitting leader and warned bloodshed must be avoided.
articles.title: South Korea presidential security chief warns against violent attempt to arrest Yoon

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: As talks continued in Qatar, the Israeli military carried out strikes across the enclave, killing at least 17 people, Palestinian medics said.
articles.title: U.S., Arab mediators make some progress in Gaza peace talks, no deal yet, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Lebanese lawmakers began voting in a presidential election on Thursday, aiming to fill a post which has been vacant since 2022, with political sources expecting army commander General Joseph Aoun to be elected.
articles.title: Lebanese lawmakers start voting on new president

articles.author: Hyunjoo Jin, Daniel Catchpole
articles.description: Before it suffered the deadliest crash in South Korea's history, budget airline Jeju Air was moving fast: racking up record passenger numbers and flying its aircraft more than domestic rivals and many of its global peers, data show.
articles.title: South Korea jet crash puts fast-growing Jeju Air's safety under scrutiny

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. President-elect Donald Trump said on Thursday a meeting was being set up between him and Russian President Vladimir Putin.
articles.title: Trump says Putin wants to meet him, meeting being set up

articles.author: Maggie Fick
articles.description: An official Palestinian tally of direct deaths in the Israel-Hamas war likely undercounted the number of casualties by 41% through the middle of 2024 as the Gaza Strip's healthcare infrastructure unravelled, according to a study published on Thursday.
articles.title: Gaza war toll likely significantly undercounts deaths, says study

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau on Wednesday said U.S. President-elect Donald Trump's talk of possibly annexing Canada was a tactic designed to distract people from the impact of his proposed tariffs.
articles.title: Trudeau says Trump talk of annexing Canada is a distraction tactic

articles.author: Kate Abnett, Alison Withers
articles.description: The world just experienced the first full year in which global temperatures exceeded 1.5C above pre-industrial times, scientists said on Friday.
articles.title: 2024 was the first year above 1.5C of global warming, scientists say
